<div style="margin-bottom:30px;" class="center">
	<h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;text-align:left;">Gaob Bika LIMS 3 Workflow</h2>
	<p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;text-align:left;padding-bottom:15px;">
    	The Bika LIMS workflow has been designed to fit all lab disciplines, and is completely conformant with ISO-17025 accreditation.
    	Bika's flexibility and open-source approach allows you to customize the system according to your lab's specific requirements.
	</p>
	<img src="workflow-diagram.png" alt="Bika LIMS" class="image-inline" title="Bika LIMS"/>
</div>
<div style="margin-bottom:30px;">
	<div style="float:left;width:47%;">
		<h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;">Why Gaob release name?</h2>
		<p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;">In the tradition of <i>Chief </i>Inkosi Bika LIMS 2 using a  title for a release, this edition is code-named<i> </i>Gaob Bika LIMS 3. Gaob, <i>King,</i> is taken from <a class="external-link" href="http://www.san.org.za/">Khoi San</a> Nama, language of <a class="external-link" href="http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/worlds-most-ancient-race-traced-in-dna-study-1677113.html">the world's first  people</a>.</p>
		
		<h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;padding-top:15px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;">Documentation</h2>
        <p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;">
            Work in progress,
            <ul style="font-size:1.2em;margin-left:15px;">
                <li><a class="external-link" href="http://demo.bikalabs.com/knowledge-centre/manual/bika-3-user-manual">User Manual</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://demo.bikalabs.com/knowledge-centre/manual/bika-3-user-manual/introduction-and-overview"><span class="state-published">Introduction and Overview</span></a></li>
                <li><a href="http://demo.bikalabs.com/knowledge-centre/manual/bika-3-user-manual/setup-and-configuration"><span class="state-published">Setup and Configuration</span></a></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        
        <h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;padding-top:15px;">Gaob Bika LIMS 3 installation</h2>
        <p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;">
            Bika 3 Gaob can be installed easily:
            <ul style="font-size:1.2em;margin-left:15px;">
              <li><a href="http://www.bikalabs.com/helpcentre/manual/bika-installation-guides/bika-on-ubuntu-linux/installing-bika-lims-3">Linux</a>.</li>
              <li><a href="http://www.bikalabs.com/helpcentre/manual/bika-installation-guides/bika-on-windows/installing-bika-lims-3-0">Windows</a>.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </div>
    <div style="float:right;width:47%;">		
        
        <h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;">Source code</h2>
        <p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;">
            If you want more power, you can also install Bika 3 Gaob by retrieving the source code directly from the repository,
            allowing easy system updates. That's the recommended installation method for developers and for users who want to test
            the latest version.
            <ul style="font-size:1.2em;margin-left:15px;">
               <li><a href="https://github.com/bikalabs/Bika-LIMS/tree/master/docs/installation.txt">Installation</a>.</li>
               <li><a href="https://github.com/bikalabs/Bika-LIMS/tree/dev">Source repository</a>.</li>
               <li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.bikalabs.com/softwarecenter/bika/releases/3.0">Bika 3 Project page</a>.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        
